



[14 October 1758]



Camp at Shawnese Cabins Saturday Octr 14th1
Parole Aberdeen
The Genl to beat to Morrow morning at 5 OClock the Assembly at 6, The Officers are to be particularly Carefull to have their Mens Arms drawn in the morning & fresh Loaded they are likewise to order their Horses to be well Securd so that they
[79]
may be ready to March at the beating of the Assembly, All the Officers may put on w[ha]t Dress they think proper to morrow. No man to Sleep without the Sentries.
